 Ecological analyses usually do not meet these expectations
These are tools instead of logical/rational entities.
They do no reveil the ultimate truth about our data.
Applying a statistical method to a research
setting requires knowledge of how the
statistical method works because the
statistical approach itself is an automaton
that does not think for itself.

models do not imply unique hypotheses.
